Except in your example, after the first draw its gone down to 1 in 8.  The conditions in the second attempt were not the same.  You have not increased availability, you have decreased the odds that you will NOT get the card you want.  Yes, you can keep drawing and eventually you'll get the winning card, even if you add cards to always make the chance 1 in 9, that's the law of averages.  But unless you add an additional card to represent another jade reaver, availability remains the same.  <br>
