 NONE of YOU  and i mean NONE of  YOU people have tossed out any meaningful numbers of  recorded to kills  to determine  either   the Jade Reaver or  the  Green scales  drop percentage....  All any of you have done is  speculate  based on  what YOUR  experiences have been. So in that light,<br>
lets Jump back to my experiences with  Both mobs.....<br>
<br>
 Sev...  I tried  1 time.  Raalf way back when kunark was still pretty new  lead  a raid on him, at that time i was still predominately playing  Bloodson (necro) and i was lvl 52 at the time.....  Was roughly  40 ppl on the  raid, a good mix of lvls thou  as  a 52 i was one of the lowest lvls attending. Raalf made groups,  we all buffed up,  Raalf pulled.  Call to attack came.. me and pet raced in.. i tried to cast a spell.  was interrupted by Sev's dragon roar  and was sent mindlessly running off in fear as was  many others.  Fear ends i race back, next  dragon roar  off i go running again. did this 5 or 6 times and  finally  enough ppl were already dead as to make the raid a   failure.  I then  FD'd and  /q'd out to clear aggro...  Logged back in and helped CR as needed. Needless to say i didn't bother trying  Sev again.<br>
<br>
Black Reavers, all told guess i've logged 200-300 hours in Com doing nothing but the reaver cycles for, guilds,friends and friends of friends  druids/rangers practically everytime i was asked.  Now the most i ever saw was 5  JR's from   1 cycle and the least i ever saw was  No  JR's in 8 hours of killing. I would also say a typical  cycle of killing actually involved killing 8-10 reavers and a excellant cycle yielded 20 or more Black Reaver pops.<br>
<br>
 Now then, based on this information, I would contend  Sev is not doable by any small to mid-guild composed  mostly of lvl 45-55 players.... Becuase of the dragon roar and apparent lack of resists to it,which we all know as you either get closer to NPC's lvl or exceed it.  your chance of resisting thier spells increases pretty much on a  graduated scale in relation to PC to NPC lvl..  <br>
   If Sev has been changed, since the time i fought him  then naturally the prior  statement is obsolete being as it is based on outdated information..... If not then  having multiple lvl 60's, well buffed resists definitely appear a Must have to actually succeed. Further investigation of Sev's loot table indicates he can drop  multiple green scales.<br>
  Now to everyone that has mentioned  &quot; Chance&quot;.......<br>
We all know &quot;random chance&quot; is a factor,anytime you kill a mob that has NOT been proved to drop  Item A  &quot;Every&quot; time.<br>
But for the life of me  i fail to see how anyone can logically  argue the  JR is tougher to get then the Green scale.  Given the  &quot;Number&quot; of chances of it dropping available from killing doing the black reaver cycle or killing Sev.<br>
  If just if,  Everyone ran into CoM  killed  ONE  Black Reaver and zoned out,  then and only then I would be tempted to agree that  that  Sev drops the green scale more often then a black Reaver drops the  JR.... Then again, logic would suggest if a Mob_A is  2 hour spawn and  Mob_B is 7 day spawn, that  MoB_B should drop loot more often because the fewer chances there is to kill Mob_B....<br>
    Now based on respawn timer and nothing else, killing Black Reavers far and away give you the most &quot;CHANCES&quot; to get loot,  regardless of what time frame you choose..  One hour,one day,one week,one year  etc.<br>
     Now based upon the number of hours i've sat in  the bazaar  item watching, chatting or otherwise  goofing off.  I have  seen  Jade  Reavers for sale  many many many times and have seen a Green scale being sold twice.... Again, my experiences, but also indicates   jade reavers enter the game HELLUA lot faster and  easier then Green Scales do.\<br>
<br>
     Now lets base drop rate on Price:<br>
<br>
       Jade Reaver  12-18kplat  or there abouts<br>
       Green  Scale  20-30kplat  or there abouts<br>
<br>
   Ayep, i see the logic now.....  Green scale drops so often and NO ONE wants it that people are damn  near giving it away..../sarcasim off .......  However,  price, at least to me, has always been a indicator of  the demand,difficulty or rarity for an item , so if thats the case a  Green Scale  is much more in demand, harder to get and rarer then  the  jade reaver is......<br>
<br>
    Hell, lets conduct a poll...  Epified  Druids or Rangers  verse Warriors......  Which class has more epic's from lvl 50-55?  How about from  55-60?    <br>
 <br>
    Overall,  all of you can  slap this topic  back and forth till the Admins either  closed this thread,  we all die of old age, or everyone accepts the fact.  That regardless of respawn time...  Random chance is the sole deciding factor on whether ANY MOB  drops anything on thier available loot or not, unless aforementioned mob  drops is a KNOWN to drop  phatlewt_01  everytime..<br>
<br>
  Enuff said,<br>
 <br>
Refomated the spacing some.<br>
