<br>
Anyways....<br>
<br>
Montyy's point... which people (*cough* Milly *cough) tend to be overlooking or just outright missing (no offense intended darlin) is that the burning of Dragons removes content from midlevel guilds.<br>
<br>
Sev pops once a week... and with MB Squads killing him... midlevel guilds are denied their shot at a significant piece of content that was designed for them.<br>
<br>
And FK... once the dragon is killed... it can be timed... so the MB Squads have an immediate leg up on others wanting a shot.<br>
<br>
CoM just can NOT be compared to Sev.  Period.  Forget the numbers of pops... and forget the drop rates.  And Milly.... let go of how twinked a team may or may not be.  It's clouding the simple fact that EACH AND EVERY TWO HOURS a full set of 6 reavers pops.<br>
<br>
EACH AND EVERY TWO HOURS a raid has a shot at their epic drops.<br>
<br>
And one more time... in case 2 wasnt enough... EACH AND EVERY TWO HOURS druids, mages, shammies and rangers have a shot at their epic drops.<br>
<br>
Will Jade Reavers, Mage Torches, etc drop?  Maybe.  Maybe not.... but the fact remains that there is at least a chance.<br>
<br>
Yes... Reavers are NOT camped 24/7... but the fact remains that they CAN be.  At any given time, you can gather a force and head to CoM.  You cant do this for Sev.<br>
<br>
As of right now (11pm est Thursday night), Sev is not up.  The Reavers are.  In 2 hours, Sev still wont be up.  The Reavers will be.  In 2 days, Sev still wont be up.  The Reavers will be.<br>
<br>
Reavers are content, and damn GOOD content for midlevel guilds.  And they are readily accessable.  Sure... Syllie, Ugg, Autty, and I killed them one day with a single group.  And sure... Montyy's twink and a group of other twinks did the same.... but the fact remains that most anyone can head to CoM and take a shot at Reavers at almost any given time.  <br>
<br>
If they're madly twinked, fine.  If they're all 60 with primals and sick armor, fine.  And if they arent twinked or high level... and they bring 3-4 groups, that's fine too.  The point (yet again) is that the content is there waiting for them.<br>
<br>
As I recall Milly... you had a very hard time getting your Reaver.  That's unfortunate, and I sympathize.  This is much like Wizards that went through hell getting a drop off of Phinny (Crysalis killed him 27 times before his staff dropped... if memory serves) or off of Venril Sathir (took me 5 killings back when he was madly contested).<br>
<br>
The point though is that you were able to gather a force, head to CoM, and kill Reavers.  <br>
<br>
Warriors cant do that with Sev.... cause he's only up once a week... and he's burned usually before a raid can get to him.<br>
<br>
In effect... if warriors want their Epics... they are all but forced to buy a scale.<br>
<br>
and THAT is what Montyy is against!  He's against being forced to purchase or (in his case) be given a green scale.  Sure, there are those that would rather just buy their Epics (I saw a full monk epic for sale the other day, and have seen other such things in the past as well) ... just as there are those that want to earn their epics themselves.  The latter would be Montyy.  He's like many warriors that would much rather face Sev in battle, try their tactics... and hope to win... than shell out 40k and buy the scale.<br>
<br>
But with no content, there is no choice.  Montyy's choice was all but made FOR him.<br>
<br>
Hell... he's MTed more Epic battles than I can count.  Dont you think he'd want a shot at MTing Sev for his own epic?<br>
<br>
Moot point now, cause he didnt have that chance... and wound up having to accept a scale rather than fight for it.... because the content of said fight was removed from the game by the burn squads.<br>
<br>
Luckily... Verant nerfed MB, and now midlevel guilds have a shot again at Sev and the other Kunark dragons.... and hopefully now... if wizards are there burning... it'll be alongside of raids... not alone... which is how it should be imo.<br>
